content:
Determine if the report supports the findings or not.
Report: The survey indicates that 45% of people prefer to buy online instead of going to the store. 
Findings: Over half of people prefer to buy online.

The report indicates that 45% of people prefer to buy online instead of going to the store. The findings state that over half of the people prefer to buy online. Since 45% is less than half, the report does not support the findings.
